{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17504790","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17504790"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T11:20:56+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T11:20:56+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2372"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"2372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/2372"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.31,0.18,0.17,0.2,0.14]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"2372"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"33633"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"2372","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/2372"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2372"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18971"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"34"},{"type":"tags","id":"64"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"404"},{"type":"tags","id":"1206"},{"type":"tags","id":"1425"},{"type":"tags","id":"2101"},{"type":"tags","id":"6275"},{"type":"tags","id":"12913"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"2084"},{"type":"contributions","id":"2341"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27423"},{"type":"contributions","id":"41630"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45440"},{"type":"contributions","id":"46094"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"33633","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/33633"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EA 75-year old woman presents to the Emergency Department with pain in her left hip after a fall. She was unable to get up off the floor and her husband called an ambulance. She is normally in good health and the only medication she takes is alendronate, together with calcium supplements. On examination there is limited movement because of the pain and the left leg appears shortened and externally rotated. An X-ray is performed (Image).\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following is the most likely diagnosis?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Subcapital fracture","Transcervical fracture","Basicervical fracture","Pertrochanteric fracture","Subtrochanteric fracture"],"correctOptions":[3],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EFractured neck of femur is a common ED presentation in elderly women and can have serious consequences with the 1 year mortality being as high as 36%. Ideally there are preventative measures in place to avoid hip fractures, however, it is crucial for the medical student to be able to diagnose one clinically as well as knowing the different types that require different treatment. Hip fractures are anatomically divided into a two regions: intracapsular (surgical neck of femur) or extra capsular (pertrochanteric or subtrochanteric). Intracapsular fractures are then further graded using the Garden Classification.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGarden 1: undisplaced, incomplete fracture\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGarden 2: undisplaced, complete fracture\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGarden 3: mildly/incompletely displaced, complete fracture\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003EGarden 4: completely displaced, complete fracture\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EWithin intracapsular there are 3 types of fracture based on location. \u003Cstrong\u003ESubcapital\u003C/strong\u003E is where the fracture line is at the base of the head of femur, just below the widest part. \u003Cstrong\u003ETranscervical\u003C/strong\u003E is a fracture through the middle of the surgical neck. \u003Cstrong\u003EBasicervical\u003C/strong\u003E is a fracture at the base of the surgical neck, just proximal to intertrochanteric fractures. The difference between intertrochanteric and pertrochanteric fractures is minimal and the two terms are frequently used synonymously.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EExtracapsular fractures as described above can be \u003Cstrong\u003Epertrochanteric\u003C/strong\u003E (fracture line dissects both greater and lesser trochanters), or \u003Cstrong\u003Esubtrochanteric\u003C/strong\u003E where the fracture line is below the intertrochanteric line up to 5cm distal the neck of femur. Beyond this is classified as a femoral shaft fracture.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EBased on the X-ray provided, the surgical neck appears intact making it extra capsular and following the cortical outline, it appears disrupted at the greater trochanter and extends across to the lesser \u2013 making this a \u003Cstrong\u003Epertrochanteric\u003C/strong\u003E fracture.\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":null,"learningPoints":["A fractured neck of femur must always be considered in the older patient who hurts their hip after a fall."],"references":["Bhandari M, Swiontkowski M. Management of Acute Hip Fracture. N Engl J Med. 2017; 377:2053-62.","Callaghan JJ, Haidukewych GJ. Subcapital fractures: a changing paradigm. J Bone Joint Surgical Br. 2012; 94: 19-21."]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"18971"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"2372"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[{"type":"media","id":"19480"}]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"media","id":"19480","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/media/19480"},"attributes":{"mimeType":"image/jpeg","url":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f2e0415f-0b0b-490a-9af6-0251819cdca3.jpg","thumbUrl":"https://app.emedici.com/storage/media/f2e